p.01703376c4a81c0e9d91: Compare a string with another one ignoring case.
p.01703376c4a81c0e9d92:
Returns a number indicating whether the reference string s2 comes before, after, or is equivalent to s1 string in sort order, ignoring the case.

Uses the `localeCompare` JavaScript` function. See: [https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)
Returns -1 if (s1 < s2), 0 if (s1 == s2), and 1 if (s1 > s2). It ignores the case.
